    sideEffects: ["Common side effects:", "Sedation: may improve with time. Avoid activity requiring mental alertness or coordination. Do not drink 90 alcohol during treatment with this medicine as it might increase the sedative effect. Do not drive or work with tools or machinery if affected. Inform prescriber at next appointment (to consider night-time dosing only)", "Constipation: bowel habit monitoring, increase your physical activity , fluid and fibre intake. May require medications. Contact prescriber if unable to pass flatus or if there is abdominal pain/discomfort (warning sign)", "Tachycardia: contact your prescriber if you experience persistent palpitation", "Weight gain: Advise on nutritional counselling (avoid low-volume, high-calorie foods) and emphasize need for physical exercise.", "Hypersalivation: often improves over time. If persistent, inform your prescriber at the next appointment. Use a towel on the pillow while sleeping and make sure to bring towel/tissue along.", "Blood pressure changes: clozapine can cause both hypotension and hypertension", "Hyperglycaemia: watch out for symptoms of increased sugar levels such as frequent urination, increased thirst and delay in wound healing Rare but serious side effects :", "Severe infection (due to drop in white cells - a condition called Neutropenia): advise to seek urgent medical assessment it patient develop flu-like symptoms", "Clozapine lowers the seizure threshold. Higher risk with higher doses. Immediately contact your prescriber in an event of seizure.", "Cardiac complications including myocarditis and cardiomyopathy . In cases where tachycardia persists at rest and is associated with fever , hypotension or chest pain, it may indicate myocarditis. Immediately contact your prescriber ."],
