    name: "Edoxaban",
    pharmacologicalGroup: "Direct Oral Anticoagulant - Factor Xa inhibitor",
    indication: "1. Prevention of stroke and systemic embolism in adult patients with nonvalvular atrial fibrillation (NVAF) with one or more risk factors, such as congestive heart failure, hypertension, and age ≥ 75 years, diabetes mellitus, prior stroke or transient ischaemic attack (TIA). a. The recommended dose is 60 mg edoxaban once daily for life-long. b. The recommended dose is 30 mg once daily in patients with one or more of the following clinical factors: - Moderate or severe renal impairment (creatinine clearance (CrCL) 15 - 50 mL/min) - Low body weight ≤ 60 kg - Concomitant use of the following P-glycoprotein (P-gp) inhibitors: ciclosporin, dronedarone, erythromycin, or ketoconazole.",
