    dosage: "0.5-1 mg sublingually may be repeated every 5 minutes until relief is obtained.",
    methodOfAdministration: "Treatment of angina 1. During an acute angina attack, the patient should rest, preferably in a sitting position. 2. Place one tablet under the tongue, allowing it to dissolve. Do not swallow or chew the tablet. 3. If pain remains, remove the undissolved tablet and place a new tablet under the tongue. The dose may be repeated every 5 minutes for a maximum of 3 times. 4. If pain persists or becomes more intense after a total dose of 3 times in 15 minutes, patient should call the ambulance or go to the hospital. Prophylaxis of angina 1. Take 1 tablet 5 to 10 minutes before exercise or exertion to prevent an attack. Do not stop taking your medication unless advised to do so by your prescriber .",
