    pharmacologicalGroup: "Antiinflammatory and antirheumatic products, non-steroids",
    indication: "Indication 1. Pain and inflammation in rheumatic disease Dosage 1. Celecoxib: 200 - 400 mg daily in 1-2 divided doses 2. Diclofenac: Initial dose of 150 mg daily. Mild or long term: 75 - 150 mg daily in 2 to 3 divided doses after food. 3. Etoricoxib: 60 - 120 mg once daily 4. Ibuprofen: 200 - 400 mg 3 times daily after food, maximum 3.2 g daily 5. Mefenamic acid: 250 - 500 mg 3 times daily after meals. 6. Meloxicam: initially 7.5 mg daily. May be increased to 15 mg daily 7. Naproxen: 500 mg initially then 250 mg every 6 - 8 hour as required To counsel based on specific medication’ s indication and dosage as prescribed by the doctor",
