    others: {"storage": "1. Store below 30 ᣞ C. 2. Keep medication in its original container , tightly sealed to protect from moisture and light. 3. Keep out of reach and sight of children.", "other_points": "Drug-drug/ Drug-food Interactions: 1. Patients should report all prescribed medications, over-the-counter medications, traditional medicines or drinks, and health supplements, both before starting therapy and during treatment. 2. They must stop taking any traditional or herbal medications, health supplements, or health drinks during treatment and should consult prescribers before starting any new medications. Precautions: 1. Advise female patients to use effective form of contraception during treatment and for 9 months 310 post-therapy 2. As for male patients with female partners, effective forms of contraception should be used during treatment and for 6 months post-therapy ."}
