    sideEffects: ["The most concerning side effect is the bleeding, which is the result of the blood being too thin. \u25cf Bruising \u25cf Nosebleeds \u25cf Bleeding gums (careful when brushing teeth \u2013 use soft toothbrush) \u25cf Pink or brown urine \u25cf Red or black stools \u25cf Vomiting blood or material that looks like coffee grounds", "Allergic reactions \u25cf Itching or hives \u25cf Swelling in face, hands, mouth, or throat \u25cf Difficulty breathing or chest tightness \u25cf Skin rash"],
    others: {"storage": "1. Store at room temperature between 15°C to 30°C", "other_points": "1. Renal impairment: To avoid usage when CrCl ≤50 mL/min 2. Moderate to severe hepatic impairment (Child-Pugh class B and C): Contraindicated."}
